Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?phase9:=20wave=2013.6.1=20patch=200068=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=E2=80=94=20keyboard=20IRQ=20counters=20in=20phase-timing=20log?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=20+=20ring-chunks=20init=20banner?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Pairs with SDL-side patch 0023 (which defines the externs this engine
patch consumes). Wave 13.6 introduced a keyboard regression on PODP
5V83 (frozen kbd, 8042 buffer-overflow beep) when ring_chunks was
bumped 4→16 to fix audio chop. This patch makes that regression
bisectable in a single CF-card swap by surfacing the relevant runtime
state in DEBUG.LOG.

Changes:

1. Renderer.cpp::_maybe_flush_phase_timing_audit() — second LOG_INFO
   line "kbd/audio block N: kbd_irq=X kbd_drain=Y ring_chunks=Z"
   immediately after the existing phase-timing line. Same block index
   so the two lines correlate via grep. Adding three more fields to
   the existing 11-line LOG_INFO would be unreadable; a separate line
   is materially easier to diff between bisect runs. The kbd counters
   are MONOTONIC (only increment, never reset) — user reads deltas
   between consecutive blocks. Per 100 flips so cost is negligible.

2. SoundManager.cpp::init() — wave-13.6.1 init banner "ring_chunks=N
   FORCE_PUMP_YIELD=on/off" placed AFTER MIX_CreateMixerDevice
   succeeds.

§5 Option A vs B decision:

   Spec §5 placed the init banner at end of Renderer::initVideo, but
   in this codebase Renderer::init runs BEFORE SoundManager::init
   (vendor/nxengine-evo/src/main.cpp lines 482 vs 510). The
   doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active symbol is set inside
   DOSSOUNDBLASTER_OpenDevice → resolve_ring_chunks(), which doesn't
   run until MIX_CreateMixerDevice fires inside SoundManager::init().
   Logging from Renderer::initVideo would always read the initializer
   value 16 regardless of env-var setting — silently misleading.

   Chose Option A (move the banner to SoundManager.cpp, after
   MIX_CreateMixerDevice success) over Option B (log the env var as
   set/unset directly via SDL_getenv) because Option A preserves
   single-source-of-truth: the SDL-side resolver normalizes garbage
   inputs (foo, empty, 0, 32) to 16, while SDL_getenv would log the
   literal string "foo" — misleading. Banner now logically sits in
   the audio init path where it belongs (it's an audio-system
   runtime knob).

Externs:

   Three extern decls (volatile uint32_t for the kbd counters; plain
   int for ring_chunks) declared in `extern "C" { ... }` blocks at
   namespace scope, NOT inline at point of use. Reason: SDL defines
   the symbols at file scope in C TUs, but a plain `extern int foo;`
   inside the surrounding NXE::Graphics::(anonymous namespace) /
   NXE::Sound namespace binds to a namespace-qualified symbol and
   the link fails. extern "C" forces unmangled global linkage to
   match the SDL-side definitions; the linkage spec is permitted
   at namespace scope (not function-block scope, ruling out the
   inline approach the spec sketched). Qualifiers match the SDL-
   side definitions byte-for-byte; mismatched qualifiers across TUs
   are UB.

Default behaviour unchanged from wave 13.6 (ring_chunks=16) when no
env vars are set. See docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §2.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Code
---
 src/graphics/Renderer.cpp  | 34 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 src/sound/SoundManager.cpp | 34 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 2 files changed, 68 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
index fd270a9..34b59c4 100644
--- a/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
+++ b/src/graphics/Renderer.cpp
@@ -643,6 +643,26 @@ struct _DrawcallTimer
   }
 };
 
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0068, Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): externs into the SDL3-DOS
+// keyboard / audio backends for the bisect-counters logged below. Defined
+// at file scope in C TUs:
+//   doskutsu_kbd_irq_count, doskutsu_kbd_drain_count
+//     vendor/SDL/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c (volatile uint32_t)
+//   doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active
+//     vendor/SDL/src/audio/dos/SDL_dosaudio_sb.c (plain int)
+// extern "C" linkage spec is required: a plain `extern int foo;` inside
+// the surrounding NXE::Graphics::(anonymous namespace) would bind to a
+// namespace-scoped symbol and the link would fail. extern "C" forces
+// unmangled global linkage to match the SDL-side definitions, and the
+// linkage spec is permitted at namespace scope in C++. Qualifiers MUST
+// match the SDL-side definitions byte-for-byte; mismatched qualifiers
+// across TUs are UB.
+extern "C" {
+  extern volatile std::uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_irq_count;
+  extern volatile std::uint32_t doskutsu_kbd_drain_count;
+  extern int doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active;
+}
+
 void _maybe_flush_phase_timing_audit()
 {
   if ((_flip_total % _dc_tally_every_flips) != 0) return;
@@ -693,6 +713,20 @@ void _maybe_flush_phase_timing_audit()
            audio_engine_ms_x10, dc_avg_us_x10,
            _abl_no_dc_timing() ? 1 : 0,
            _abl_cache_winsurf() ? 1 : 0);
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0068, Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): keyboard-IRQ-delivery
+  // counters and active audio ring-chunks value, logged alongside the
+  // existing phase-timing block so each measurement run self-describes.
+  // Counters bumped in vendor/SDL/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c (irq +
+  // pump drain). ring_chunks resolved in SDL_dosaudio_sb.c on first
+  // OpenDevice. Externs declared at namespace scope just above; see
+  // their comment block for the linkage rationale. The kbd counters
+  // are MONOTONIC across the run (never reset) — read deltas between
+  // consecutive blocks.
+  LOG_INFO("kbd/audio block {}: kbd_irq={} kbd_drain={} ring_chunks={}",
+           _dc_block_idx,
+           (unsigned long)doskutsu_kbd_irq_count,
+           (unsigned long)doskutsu_kbd_drain_count,
+           doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active);
   _drawcall_accum_ns_block = 0;
   _drawcall_count_block = 0;
   _flip_inner_accum_ns_block = 0;
diff --git a/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp b/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
index d5fb824..3191cc6 100644
--- a/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
+++ b/src/sound/SoundManager.cpp
@@ -22,6 +22,18 @@ namespace NXE
 namespace Sound
 {
 
+// DOS-PORT (patch 0068, Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): extern into the SDL3-DOS
+// audio backend for the wave-13.6.1 init banner below. Defined at file
+// scope in vendor/SDL/src/audio/dos/SDL_dosaudio_sb.c (plain int, set
+// on first OpenDevice). extern "C" linkage spec is required: a plain
+// `extern int foo;` inside the surrounding NXE::Sound namespace would
+// bind to a namespace-scoped symbol and the link would fail. extern
+// "C" forces unmangled global linkage; the linkage spec is permitted
+// at namespace scope in C++.
+extern "C" {
+  extern int doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active;
+}
+
 SoundManager::SoundManager() {}
 SoundManager::~SoundManager() {}
 
@@ -81,6 +93,28 @@ bool SoundManager::init()
     return false;
   }
 
+  // DOS-PORT (patch 0068, Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): consolidated runtime-knob
+  // banner so DEBUG.LOG records which ring-chunks value and yield mode a
+  // given iter ran with. ring_chunks is sourced from SDL_dosaudio_sb.c's
+  // resolve_ring_chunks() via the extern declared at namespace scope
+  // above — single source of truth. Placed here (NOT in Renderer::
+  // initVideo as the original spec §5 suggested) because in this code-
+  // base Renderer::init runs BEFORE SoundManager::init (see vendor/
+  // nxengine-evo/src/main.cpp lines 482 vs 510), so logging from init-
+  // Video would always read the initializer value 16 regardless of
+  // env-var setting. By the time MIX_CreateMixerDevice returns success-
+  // fully above, DOSSOUNDBLASTER_OpenDevice has run and the symbol
+  // reflects the resolved value.
+  {
+    const char *force_yield = SDL_getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_PUMP_YIELD");
+    const bool yield_forced = force_yield && force_yield[0] == '1' && force_yield[1] == 0;
+    LOG_INFO("wave-13.6.1: ring_chunks={} FORCE_PUMP_YIELD={} "
+             "(set SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_AUDIO_RING_CHUNKS=4|8|16 to override; "
+             "default 16 matches wave 13.6 behaviour)",
+             doskutsu_audio_ring_chunks_active,
+             yield_forced ? "on" : "off");
+  }
+
   // DOS-PORT: Mix_AllocateChannels(64) is gone in SDL3_mixer — the new
   // API has no fixed channel count. Tracks are created on-demand by
   // Pixtone via MIX_CreateTrack(). The 64-channel cap is preserved by
